Hi, Not true. 
Amaya installer shows you the directory in which the directory root of the Amaya tree will be installed and you are free to modify it. 
The root directory in Amaya in Thot. 
if, for instance, you shose C:\Programs Files, Amaya will be intalled in C:\Program Files\Thot. 
This is not typical to Amaya, but always the case for any program. 
Here you are in right place. 
